reviews.review_text: Very enjoyable show Many have said this is one of the best of '93, it does have it's moments,but there are other shows that raise  above this one. This one starts off strong with a nice 1/2 Step, an early set So Many Roads and the rest of the set is quite nice, High Time & Deal are  highlights. Set two has a very strong Fire, a sweet Ship of Fools.If you are a  fan of  Wave to the Wind, as I am, you will like this version. The transition into Truckin' is  rough but they rebound nicely. The post  drum is very good with an amazing Heaven's Door which is the highlight of the show.

Spring 1993 Wow the Sound Quality is Top Notch. Would love to hear more mixes like this from 1993. A really underrated year. The band  showed flashes of brilliance but had a hard time sustaining it. 
When they were on they put down some ridiculously hot renditions.

Solid Show 

Ship of Fools> Truckin from this nights performance I consider to among the all time best
Attics of my Mind! My penultimate show. Great run, love Attics too!
